47FILE *openProcess(const QString &command)
48{
49#if defined(Q_OS_WIN32)
50 QString processedCommand = u'\"' + command + u'\"';
51#else
52 const QString& processedCommand = command;
53#endif
54
55 return popen(command: processedCommand.toLocal8Bit().constData(), QT_POPEN_READ);
56}

235QString architectureFromName(const QString &name)
236{
237 QRegularExpression architecture(QStringLiteral("_(armeabi-v7a|arm64-v8a|x86|x86_64).so$"));
238 auto match = architecture.match(subject: name);
239 if (!match.hasMatch())
240 return {};
241 return match.captured(nth: 1);
242}

270{
271 return execSuffixAppended(path: "%1/toolchains/%2/prebuilt/%3/bin/llvm-readobj"_L1

277QString fileArchitecture(const Options &options, const QString &path)
278{
279 auto arch = architectureFromName(name: path);
280 if (!arch.isEmpty())
281 return arch;
282
283 QString readElf = llvmReadobjPath(options);
284 if (!QFile::exists(fileName: readElf)) {
285 fprintf(stderr, format: "Command does not exist: %s\n", qPrintable(readElf));
286 return {};
287 }
288
289 readElf = "%1 --needed-libs %2"_L1.arg(args: shellQuote(arg: readElf), args: shellQuote(arg: path));
290
291 FILE *readElfCommand = openProcess(command: readElf);
292 if (!readElfCommand) {
293 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot execute command %s\n", qPrintable(readElf));
294 return {};
295 }
296
297 char buffer[512];
298 while (fgets(s: buffer, n: sizeof(buffer), stream: readElfCommand) != nullptr) {
299 QByteArray line = QByteArray::fromRawData(data: buffer, size: qstrlen(str: buffer));
300 QString library;
301 line = line.trimmed();
302 if (line.startsWith(bv: "Arch: ")) {
303 auto it = elfArchitectures.find(key: line.mid(index: 6));
304 pclose(stream: readElfCommand);
305 return it != elfArchitectures.constEnd() ? QString::fromLatin1(ba: it.value()) : QString{};
306 }
307 }
308 pclose(stream: readElfCommand);
309 return {};
310}

312bool checkArchitecture(const Options &options, const QString &fileName)
313{
314 return fileArchitecture(options, path: fileName) == options.currentArchitecture;
315}

317void deleteMissingFiles(const Options &options, const QDir &srcDir, const QDir &dstDir)
318{
319 if (options.verbose)
320 fprintf(stdout, format: "Delete missing files %s %s\n", qPrintable(srcDir.absolutePath()), qPrintable(dstDir.absolutePath()));
321
322 const QFileInfoList srcEntries = srcDir.entryInfoList(filters: QDir::NoDotAndDotDot | QDir::Files | QDir::Dirs);
323 const QFileInfoList dstEntries = dstDir.entryInfoList(filters: QDir::NoDotAndDotDot | QDir::Files | QDir::Dirs);
324 for (const QFileInfo &dst : dstEntries) {
325 bool found = false;
326 for (const QFileInfo &src : srcEntries)
327 if (dst.fileName() == src.fileName()) {
328 if (dst.isDir())
329 deleteMissingFiles(options, srcDir: src.absoluteFilePath(), dstDir: dst.absoluteFilePath());
330 found = true;
331 break;
332 }
333
334 if (!found) {
335 if (options.verbose)
336 fprintf(stdout, format: "%s not found in %s, removing it.\n", qPrintable(dst.fileName()), qPrintable(srcDir.absolutePath()));
337
338 if (dst.isDir())
339 QDir{dst.absolutePath()}.removeRecursively();
340 else
341 QFile::remove(fileName: dst.absoluteFilePath());
342 }
343 }
344 fflush(stdout);
345}

347Options parseOptions()
348{
349 Options options;
350
351 QStringList arguments = QCoreApplication::arguments();
352 for (int i=0; i<arguments.size(); ++i) {
353 const QString &argument = arguments.at(i);
354 if (argument.compare(other: "--output"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
355 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
356 options.helpRequested = true;
357 else
358 options.outputDirectory = arguments.at(i: ++i).trimmed();
359 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--input"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
360 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
361 options.helpRequested = true;
362 else
363 options.inputFileName = arguments.at(i: ++i);
364 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--aab"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
365 options.buildAAB = true;
366 options.build = true;
367 } else if (!options.buildAAB && argument.compare(other: "--no-build"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
368 options.build = false;
369 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--install"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
370 options.installApk = true;
371 options.uninstallApk = true;
372 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--reinstall"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
373 options.installApk = true;
374 options.uninstallApk = false;
375 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--android-platform"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
376 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
377 options.helpRequested = true;
378 else
379 options.androidPlatform = arguments.at(i: ++i);
380 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--help"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
381 options.helpRequested = true;
382 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--verbose"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
383 options.verbose = true;
384 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--deployment"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
385 if (i + 1 == arguments.size()) {
386 options.helpRequested = true;
387 } else {
388 QString deploymentMechanism = arguments.at(i: ++i);
389 if (deploymentMechanism.compare(other: "bundled"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
390 options.deploymentMechanism = Options::Bundled;
391 } else if (deploymentMechanism.compare(other: "unbundled"_L1,
392 cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
393 options.deploymentMechanism = Options::Unbundled;
394 } else {
395 fprintf(stderr, format: "Unrecognized deployment mechanism: %s\n", qPrintable(deploymentMechanism));
396 options.helpRequested = true;
397 }
398 }
399 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--device"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
400 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
401 options.helpRequested = true;
402 else
403 options.installLocation = arguments.at(i: ++i);
404 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--release"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
405 options.releasePackage = true;
406 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--jdk"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
407 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
408 options.helpRequested = true;
409 else
410 options.jdkPath = arguments.at(i: ++i);
411 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--apk"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
412 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
413 options.helpRequested = true;
414 else
415 options.apkPath = arguments.at(i: ++i);
416 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--depfile"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
417 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
418 options.helpRequested = true;
419 else
420 options.depFilePath = arguments.at(i: ++i);
421 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--builddir"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
422 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
423 options.helpRequested = true;
424 else
425 options.buildDirectory = arguments.at(i: ++i);
426 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--sign"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
427 if (i + 2 >= arguments.size()) {
428 const QString keyStore = qEnvironmentVariable(varName: "QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_PATH");
429 const QString storeAlias = qEnvironmentVariable(varName: "QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_ALIAS");
430 if (keyStore.isEmpty() || storeAlias.isEmpty()) {
431 options.helpRequested = true;
432 fprintf(stderr, format: "Package signing path and alias values are not specified.\n");
433 } else {
434 fprintf(stdout,
435 format: "Using package signing path and alias values found from the "
436 "environment variables.\n");
437 options.keyStore = keyStore;
438 options.keyStoreAlias = storeAlias;
439 }
440 } else if (!arguments.at(i: i + 1).startsWith(s: "--"_L1) &&
441 !arguments.at(i: i + 2).startsWith(s: "--"_L1)) {
442 options.keyStore = arguments.at(i: ++i);
443 options.keyStoreAlias = arguments.at(i: ++i);
444 } else {
445 options.helpRequested = true;
446 fprintf(stderr, format: "Package signing path and alias values are not "
447 "specified.\n");
448 }
449
450 // Do not override if the passwords are provided through arguments
451 if (options.keyStorePassword.isEmpty()) {
452 fprintf(stdout, format: "Using package signing store password found from the environment "
453 "variable.\n");
454 options.keyStorePassword = qEnvironmentVariable(varName: "QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_STORE_PASS");
455 }
456 if (options.keyPass.isEmpty()) {
457 fprintf(stdout, format: "Using package signing key password found from the environment "
458 "variable.\n");
459 options.keyPass = qEnvironmentVariable(varName: "QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_KEY_PASS");
460 }
461 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--storepass"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
462 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
463 options.helpRequested = true;
464 else
465 options.keyStorePassword = arguments.at(i: ++i);
466 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--storetype"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
467 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
468 options.helpRequested = true;
469 else
470 options.storeType = arguments.at(i: ++i);
471 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--keypass"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
472 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
473 options.helpRequested = true;
474 else
475 options.keyPass = arguments.at(i: ++i);
476 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--sigfile"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
477 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
478 options.helpRequested = true;
479 else
480 options.sigFile = arguments.at(i: ++i);
481 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--digestalg"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
482 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
483 options.helpRequested = true;
484 else
485 options.digestAlg = arguments.at(i: ++i);
486 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--sigalg"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
487 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
488 options.helpRequested = true;
489 else
490 options.sigAlg = arguments.at(i: ++i);
491 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--tsa"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
492 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
493 options.helpRequested = true;
494 else
495 options.tsaUrl = arguments.at(i: ++i);
496 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--tsacert"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
497 if (i + 1 == arguments.size())
498 options.helpRequested = true;
499 else
500 options.tsaCert = arguments.at(i: ++i);
501 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--internalsf"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
502 options.internalSf = true;
503 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--sectionsonly"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
504 options.sectionsOnly = true;
505 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--protected"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
506 options.protectedAuthenticationPath = true;
507 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--aux-mode"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
508 options.auxMode = true;
509 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--qml-importscanner-binary"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
510 options.qmlImportScannerBinaryPath = arguments.at(i: ++i).trimmed();
511 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--no-rcc-bundle-cleanup"_L1,
512 cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
513 options.noRccBundleCleanup = true;
514 } else if (argument.compare(other: "--copy-dependencies-only"_L1,
515 cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
516 options.copyDependenciesOnly = true;
517 }
518 }
519
520 if (options.buildDirectory.isEmpty() && !options.depFilePath.isEmpty())
521 options.helpRequested = true;
522
523 if (options.inputFileName.isEmpty())
524 options.inputFileName = "android-%1-deployment-settings.json"_L1.arg(args: QDir::current().dirName());
525
526 options.timing = qEnvironmentVariableIsSet(varName: "ANDROIDDEPLOYQT_TIMING_OUTPUT");
527
528 if (!QDir::current().mkpath(dirPath: options.outputDirectory)) {
529 fprintf(stderr, format: "Invalid output directory: %s\n", qPrintable(options.outputDirectory));
530 options.outputDirectory.clear();
531 } else {
532 options.outputDirectory = QFileInfo(options.outputDirectory).canonicalFilePath();
533 if (!options.outputDirectory.endsWith(c: u'/'))
534 options.outputDirectory += u'/';
535 }
536
537 return options;
538}

540void printHelp()
541{
542 fprintf(stderr, format: R"(
543Syntax: androiddeployqt --output <destination> [options]
544
545Creates an Android package in the build directory <destination> and
546builds it into an .apk file.
547
548Optional arguments:
549 --input <inputfile>: Reads <inputfile> for options generated by
550 qmake. A default file name based on the current working
551 directory will be used if nothing else is specified.
552
553 --deployment <mechanism>: Supported deployment mechanisms:
554 bundled (default): Includes Qt files in stand-alone package.
555 unbundled: Assumes native libraries are present on the device
556 and does not include them in the APK.
557
558 --aab: Build an Android App Bundle.
559
560 --no-build: Do not build the package, it is useful to just install
561 a package previously built.
562
563 --install: Installs apk to device/emulator. By default this step is
564 not taken. If the application has previously been installed on
565 the device, it will be uninstalled first.
566
567 --reinstall: Installs apk to device/emulator. By default this step
568 is not taken. If the application has previously been installed on
569 the device, it will be overwritten, but its data will be left
570 intact.
571
572 --device [device ID]: Use specified device for deployment. Default
573 is the device selected by default by adb.
574
575 --android-platform <platform>: Builds against the given android
576 platform. By default, the highest available version will be
577 used.
578
579 --release: Builds a package ready for release. By default, the
580 package will be signed with a debug key.
581
582 --sign <url/to/keystore> <alias>: Signs the package with the
583 specified keystore, alias and store password.
584 Optional arguments for use with signing:
585 --storepass <password>: Keystore password.
586 --storetype <type>: Keystore type.
587 --keypass <password>: Password for private key (if different
588 from keystore password.)
589 --sigfile <file>: Name of .SF/.DSA file.
590 --digestalg <name>: Name of digest algorithm. Default is
591 "SHA1".
592 --sigalg <name>: Name of signature algorithm. Default is
593 "SHA1withRSA".
594 --tsa <url>: Location of the Time Stamping Authority.
595 --tsacert <alias>: Public key certificate for TSA.
596 --internalsf: Include the .SF file inside the signature block.
597 --sectionsonly: Don't compute hash of entire manifest.
598 --protected: Keystore has protected authentication path.
599 --jarsigner: Deprecated, ignored.
600
601 NOTE: To conceal the keystore information, the environment variables
602 QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_PATH, and QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_ALIAS are used to
603 set the values keysotore and alias respectively.
604 Also the environment variables QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_STORE_PASS,
605 and QT_ANDROID_KEYSTORE_KEY_PASS are used to set the store and key
606 passwords respectively. This option needs only the --sign parameter.
607
608 --jdk <path/to/jdk>: Used to find the jarsigner tool when used
609 in combination with the --release argument. By default,
610 an attempt is made to detect the tool using the JAVA_HOME and
611 PATH environment variables, in that order.
612
613 --qml-import-paths: Specify additional search paths for QML
614 imports.
615
616 --verbose: Prints out information during processing.
617
618 --no-generated-assets-cache: Do not pregenerate the entry list for
619 the assets file engine.
620
621 --aux-mode: Operate in auxiliary mode. This will only copy the
622 dependencies into the build directory and update the XML templates.
623 The project will not be built or installed.
624
625 --apk <path/where/to/copy/the/apk>: Path where to copy the built apk.
626
627 --qml-importscanner-binary <path/to/qmlimportscanner>: Override the
628 default qmlimportscanner binary path. By default the
629 qmlimportscanner binary is located using the Qt directory
630 specified in the input file.
631
632 --depfile <path/to/depfile>: Output a dependency file.
633
634 --builddir <path/to/build/directory>: build directory. Necessary when
635 generating a depfile because ninja requires relative paths.
636
637 --no-rcc-bundle-cleanup: skip cleaning rcc bundle directory after
638 running androiddeployqt. This option simplifies debugging of
639 the resource bundle content, but it should not be used when deploying
640 a project, since it litters the 'assets' directory.
641
642 --copy-dependencies-only: resolve application dependencies and stop
643 deploying process after all libraries and resources that the
644 application depends on have been copied.
645
646 --help: Displays this information.
647)");
648}

650// Since strings compared will all start with the same letters,
651// sorting by length and then alphabetically within each length
652// gives the natural order.
653bool quasiLexicographicalReverseLessThan(const QFileInfo &fi1, const QFileInfo &fi2)
654{
655 QString s1 = fi1.baseName();
656 QString s2 = fi2.baseName();
657
658 if (s1.size() == s2.size())
659 return s1 > s2;
660 else
661 return s1.size() > s2.size();
662}

664// Files which contain templates that need to be overwritten by build data should be overwritten every
665// time.
666bool alwaysOverwritableFile(const QString &fileName)
667{
668 return (fileName.endsWith(s: "/res/values/libs.xml"_L1)
669 || fileName.endsWith(s: "/AndroidManifest.xml"_L1)
670 || fileName.endsWith(s: "/res/values/strings.xml"_L1)
671 || fileName.endsWith(s: "/src/org/qtproject/qt/android/bindings/QtActivity.java"_L1));
672}

675bool copyFileIfNewer(const QString &sourceFileName,
676 const QString &destinationFileName,
677 const Options &options,
678 bool forceOverwrite = false)
679{
680 dependenciesForDepfile << sourceFileName;
681 if (QFile::exists(fileName: destinationFileName)) {
682 QFileInfo destinationFileInfo(destinationFileName);
683 QFileInfo sourceFileInfo(sourceFileName);
684
685 if (!forceOverwrite
686 && sourceFileInfo.lastModified() <= destinationFileInfo.lastModified()
687 && !alwaysOverwritableFile(fileName: destinationFileName)) {
688 if (options.verbose)
689 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Skipping file %s. Same or newer file already in place.\n", qPrintable(sourceFileName));
690 return true;
691 } else {
692 if (!QFile(destinationFileName).remove()) {
693 fprintf(stderr, format: "Can't remove old file: %s\n", qPrintable(destinationFileName));
694 return false;
695 }
696 }
697 }
698
699 if (!QDir().mkpath(dirPath: QFileInfo(destinationFileName).path())) {
700 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot make output directory for %s.\n", qPrintable(destinationFileName));
701 return false;
702 }
703
704 if (!QFile::exists(fileName: destinationFileName) && !QFile::copy(fileName: sourceFileName, newName: destinationFileName)) {
705 fprintf(stderr, format: "Failed to copy %s to %s.\n", qPrintable(sourceFileName), qPrintable(destinationFileName));
706 return false;
707 } else if (options.verbose) {
708 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Copied %s\n", qPrintable(destinationFileName));
709 fflush(stdout);
710 }
711 return true;
712}

714QString cleanPackageName(QString packageName)
715{
716 auto isLegalChar = [] (QChar c) -> bool {
717 ushort ch = c.unicode();
718 return (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9') ||
719 (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z') ||
720 (ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z') ||
721 ch == '.';
722 };
723 for (QChar &c : packageName) {
724 if (!isLegalChar(c))
725 c = u'_';
726 }
727
728 static QStringList keywords;
729 if (keywords.isEmpty()) {
730 keywords << "abstract"_L1 << "continue"_L1 << "for"_L1
731 << "new"_L1 << "switch"_L1 << "assert"_L1
732 << "default"_L1 << "if"_L1 << "package"_L1
733 << "synchronized"_L1 << "boolean"_L1 << "do"_L1
734 << "goto"_L1 << "private"_L1 << "this"_L1
735 << "break"_L1 << "double"_L1 << "implements"_L1
736 << "protected"_L1 << "throw"_L1 << "byte"_L1
737 << "else"_L1 << "import"_L1 << "public"_L1
738 << "throws"_L1 << "case"_L1 << "enum"_L1
739 << "instanceof"_L1 << "return"_L1 << "transient"_L1
740 << "catch"_L1 << "extends"_L1 << "int"_L1
741 << "short"_L1 << "try"_L1 << "char"_L1
742 << "final"_L1 << "interface"_L1 << "static"_L1
743 << "void"_L1 << "class"_L1 << "finally"_L1
744 << "long"_L1 << "strictfp"_L1 << "volatile"_L1
745 << "const"_L1 << "float"_L1 << "native"_L1
746 << "super"_L1 << "while"_L1;
747 }
748
749 // No keywords
750 qsizetype index = -1;
751 while (index < packageName.size()) {
752 qsizetype next = packageName.indexOf(c: u'.', from: index + 1);
753 if (next == -1)
754 next = packageName.size();
755 QString word = packageName.mid(position: index + 1, n: next - index - 1);
756 if (!word.isEmpty()) {
757 QChar c = word[0];
758 if ((c >= u'0' && c <= u'9') || c == u'_') {
759 packageName.insert(i: index + 1, c: u'a');
760 index = next + 1;
761 continue;
762 }
763 }
764 if (keywords.contains(str: word)) {
765 packageName.insert(i: next, s: "_"_L1);
766 index = next + 1;
767 } else {
768 index = next;
769 }
770 }
771
772 return packageName;
773}

775QString detectLatestAndroidPlatform(const QString &sdkPath)
776{
777 QDir dir(sdkPath + "/platforms"_L1);
778 if (!dir.exists()) {
779 fprintf(stderr, format: "Directory %s does not exist\n", qPrintable(dir.absolutePath()));
780 return QString();
781 }
782
783 QFileInfoList fileInfos = dir.entryInfoList(filters: QDir::Dirs | QDir::NoDotAndDotDot);
784 if (fileInfos.isEmpty()) {
785 fprintf(stderr, format: "No platforms found in %s", qPrintable(dir.absolutePath()));
786 return QString();
787 }
788
789 std::sort(first: fileInfos.begin(), last: fileInfos.end(), comp: quasiLexicographicalReverseLessThan);
790
791 QFileInfo latestPlatform = fileInfos.first();
792 return latestPlatform.baseName();
793}

795QString packageNameFromAndroidManifest(const QString &androidManifestPath)
796{
797 QFile androidManifestXml(androidManifestPath);
798 if (androidManifestXml.open(flags: QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
799 QXmlStreamReader reader(&androidManifestXml);
800 while (!reader.atEnd()) {
801 reader.readNext();
802 if (reader.isStartElement() && reader.name() == "manifest"_L1)
803 return cleanPackageName(packageName: reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "package"_L1).toString());
804 }
805 }
806 return {};

809bool parseCmakeBoolean(const QJsonValue &value)
810{
811 const QString stringValue = value.toString();
812 return (stringValue.compare(s: QString::fromUtf8(utf8: "true"), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)
813 || stringValue.compare(s: QString::fromUtf8(utf8: "on"), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)
814 || stringValue.compare(s: QString::fromUtf8(utf8: "yes"), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)
815 || stringValue.compare(s: QString::fromUtf8(utf8: "y"), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)
816 || stringValue.toInt() > 0);
817}

820{

886 // We assume Qt > 5.14 where all architectures are in the same directory.

1333 && !copyFileIfNewer(sourceFileName: extraLib, destinationFileName: destinationFile, options: *options)) {

1343{

1397
1398bool updateFile(const QString &fileName, const QHash<QString, QString> &replacements)
1399{
1400 QFile inputFile(fileName);
1401 if (!inputFile.open(flags: QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
1402 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot open %s for reading.\n", qPrintable(fileName));
1403 return false;
1404 }
1405
1406 // All the files we are doing substitutes in are quite small. If this
1407 // ever changes, this code should be updated to be more conservative.
1408 QByteArray contents = inputFile.readAll();
1409
1410 bool hasReplacements = false;
1411 QHash<QString, QString>::const_iterator it;
1412 for (it = replacements.constBegin(); it != replacements.constEnd(); ++it) {
1413 if (it.key() == it.value())
1414 continue; // Nothing to actually replace
1415
1416 forever {
1417 int index = contents.indexOf(bv: it.key().toUtf8());
1418 if (index >= 0) {
1419 contents.replace(index, len: it.key().size(), s: it.value().toUtf8());
1420 hasReplacements = true;
1421 } else {
1422 break;
1423 }
1424 }
1425 }
1426
1427 if (hasReplacements) {
1428 inputFile.close();
1429
1430 if (!inputFile.open(flags: QIODevice::WriteOnly)) {
1431 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot open %s for writing.\n", qPrintable(fileName));
1432 return false;
1433 }
1434
1435 inputFile.write(data: contents);
1436 }
1437
1438 return true;
1439
1440}
1441
1442bool updateLibsXml(Options *options)
1443{
1444 if (options->verbose)
1445 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- res/values/libs.xml\n");
1446
1447 QString fileName = options->outputDirectory + "/res/values/libs.xml"_L1;
1448 if (!QFile::exists(fileName)) {
1449 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot find %s in prepared packaged. This file is required.\n", qPrintable(fileName));
1450 return false;
1451 }
1452
1453 QString qtLibs;
1454 QString allLocalLibs;
1455 QString extraLibs;
1456
1457 for (auto it = options->architectures.constBegin(); it != options->architectures.constEnd(); ++it) {
1458 if (!it->enabled)
1459 continue;
1460 QString libsPath = "libs/"_L1 + it.key() + u'/';
1461
1462 qtLibs += " <item>%1;%2</item>\n"_L1.arg(args: it.key(), args&: options->stdCppName);
1463 for (const Options::BundledFile &bundledFile : options->bundledFiles[it.key()]) {
1464 if (bundledFile.second.startsWith(s: "lib/lib"_L1)) {
1465 if (!bundledFile.second.endsWith(s: ".so"_L1)) {
1466 fprintf(stderr,
1467 format: "The bundled library %s doesn't end with .so. Android only supports "
1468 "versionless libraries ending with the .so suffix.\n",
1469 qPrintable(bundledFile.second));
1470 return false;
1471 }
1472 QString s = bundledFile.second.mid(position: sizeof("lib/lib") - 1);
1473 s.chop(n: sizeof(".so") - 1);
1474 qtLibs += " <item>%1;%2</item>\n"_L1.arg(args: it.key(), args&: s);
1475 }
1476 }
1477
1478 if (!options->archExtraLibs[it.key()].isEmpty()) {
1479 for (const QString &extraLib : options->archExtraLibs[it.key()]) {
1480 QFileInfo extraLibInfo(extraLib);
1481 if (extraLibInfo.fileName().startsWith(s: "lib"_L1)) {
1482 if (!extraLibInfo.fileName().endsWith(s: ".so"_L1)) {
1483 fprintf(stderr,
1484 format: "The library %s doesn't end with .so. Android only supports "
1485 "versionless libraries ending with the .so suffix.\n",
1486 qPrintable(extraLibInfo.fileName()));
1487 return false;
1488 }
1489 QString name = extraLibInfo.fileName().mid(position: sizeof("lib") - 1);
1490 name.chop(n: sizeof(".so") - 1);
1491 extraLibs += " <item>%1;%2</item>\n"_L1.arg(args: it.key(), args&: name);
1492 }
1493 }
1494 }
1495
1496 QStringList localLibs;
1497 localLibs = options->localLibs[it.key()];
1498 // If .pro file overrides dependency detection, we need to see which platform plugin they picked
1499 if (localLibs.isEmpty()) {
1500 QString plugin;
1501 for (const QtDependency &qtDependency : options->qtDependencies[it.key()]) {
1502 if (qtDependency.relativePath.endsWith(s: "libqtforandroid.so"_L1)
1503 || qtDependency.relativePath.endsWith(s: "libqtforandroidGL.so"_L1)) {
1504 if (!plugin.isEmpty() && plugin != qtDependency.relativePath) {
1505 fprintf(stderr, format: "Both platform plugins libqtforandroid.so and libqtforandroidGL.so included in package. Please include only one.\n");
1506 return false;
1507 }
1508
1509 plugin = qtDependency.relativePath;
1510 }
1511 if (qtDependency.relativePath.contains(
1512 s: QString::asprintf(format: "libQt%dOpenGL", QT_VERSION_MAJOR))
1513 || qtDependency.relativePath.contains(
1514 s: QString::asprintf(format: "libQt%dQuick", QT_VERSION_MAJOR))) {
1515 options->usesOpenGL |= true;
1516 break;
1517 }
1518 }
1519
1520 if (plugin.isEmpty()) {
1521 fflush(stdout);
1522 fprintf(stderr, format: "No platform plugin, neither libqtforandroid.so or libqtforandroidGL.so, included in package. Please include one.\n");
1523 fflush(stderr);
1524 return false;
1525 }
1526
1527 localLibs.append(t: plugin);
1528 if (options->verbose)
1529 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Using platform plugin %s\n", qPrintable(plugin));
1530 }
1531
1532 // remove all paths
1533 for (auto &lib : localLibs) {
1534 if (lib.endsWith(s: ".so"_L1))
1535 lib = lib.mid(position: lib.lastIndexOf(c: u'/') + 1);
1536 }
1537 allLocalLibs += " <item>%1;%2</item>\n"_L1.arg(args: it.key(), args: localLibs.join(sep: u':'));
1538 }
1539
1540 options->initClasses.removeDuplicates();
1541
1542 QHash<QString, QString> replacements;
1543 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%INSERT_QT_LIBS%% -->")] += qtLibs.trimmed();
1544 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%INSERT_LOCAL_LIBS%% -->")] = allLocalLibs.trimmed();
1545 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%INSERT_EXTRA_LIBS%% -->")] = extraLibs.trimmed();
1546 const QString initClasses = options->initClasses.join(sep: u':');
1547 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%INSERT_INIT_CLASSES%% -->")] = initClasses;
1548
1549 // Set BUNDLE_LOCAL_QT_LIBS based on the deployment used
1550 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%BUNDLE_LOCAL_QT_LIBS%% -->")]
1551 = isDeployment(options, deployment: Options::Unbundled) ? "0"_L1 : "1"_L1;
1552 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%USE_LOCAL_QT_LIBS%% -->")] = "1"_L1;
1553 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%SYSTEM_LIBS_PREFIX%% -->")] =
1554 isDeployment(options, deployment: Options::Unbundled) ? options->systemLibsPath : QStringLiteral("");
1555
1556 if (!updateFile(fileName, replacements))
1557 return false;
1558
1559 return true;
1560}

1591bool updateAndroidManifest(Options &options)
1592{
1593 if (options.verbose)
1594 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- AndroidManifest.xml \n");
1595
1596 QHash<QString, QString> replacements;
1597 replacements[QStringLiteral("-- %%INSERT_APP_NAME%% --")] = options.applicationBinary;
1598 replacements[QStringLiteral("-- %%INSERT_APP_ARGUMENTS%% --")] = options.applicationArguments;
1599 replacements[QStringLiteral("-- %%INSERT_APP_LIB_NAME%% --")] = options.applicationBinary;
1600 replacements[QStringLiteral("-- %%INSERT_VERSION_NAME%% --")] = options.versionName;
1601 replacements[QStringLiteral("-- %%INSERT_VERSION_CODE%% --")] = options.versionCode;
1602 replacements[QStringLiteral("package=\"org.qtproject.example\"")] = "package=\"%1\""_L1.arg(args&: options.packageName);
1603
1604 QString permissions;
1605 for (const QString &permission : std::as_const(t&: options.permissions))
1606 permissions += " <uses-permission android:name=\"%1\" />\n"_L1.arg(args: permission);
1607 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%INSERT_PERMISSIONS -->")] = permissions.trimmed();
1608
1609 QString features;
1610 for (const QString &feature : std::as_const(t&: options.features))
1611 features += " <uses-feature android:name=\"%1\" android:required=\"false\" />\n"_L1.arg(args: feature);
1612 if (options.usesOpenGL)
1613 features += " <uses-feature android:glEsVersion=\"0x00020000\" android:required=\"true\" />"_L1;
1614
1615 replacements[QStringLiteral("<!-- %%INSERT_FEATURES -->")] = features.trimmed();
1616
1617 QString androidManifestPath = options.outputDirectory + "/AndroidManifest.xml"_L1;
1618 if (!updateFile(fileName: androidManifestPath, replacements))
1619 return false;
1620
1621 // read the package, min & target sdk API levels from manifest file.
1622 bool checkOldAndroidLabelString = false;
1623 QFile androidManifestXml(androidManifestPath);
1624 if (androidManifestXml.exists()) {
1625 if (!androidManifestXml.open(flags: QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
1626 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot open %s for reading.\n", qPrintable(androidManifestPath));
1627 return false;
1628 }
1629
1630 QXmlStreamReader reader(&androidManifestXml);
1631 while (!reader.atEnd()) {
1632 reader.readNext();
1633
1634 if (reader.isStartElement()) {
1635 if (reader.name() == "manifest"_L1) {
1636 if (!reader.attributes().hasAttribute(qualifiedName: "package"_L1)) {
1637 fprintf(stderr, format: "Invalid android manifest file: %s\n", qPrintable(androidManifestPath));
1638 return false;
1639 }
1640 options.packageName = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "package"_L1).toString();
1641 } else if (reader.name() == "uses-sdk"_L1) {
1642 if (reader.attributes().hasAttribute(qualifiedName: "android:minSdkVersion"_L1))
1643 if (reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "android:minSdkVersion"_L1).toInt() < 23) {
1644 fprintf(stderr, format: "Invalid minSdkVersion version, minSdkVersion must be >= 23\n");
1645 return false;
1646 }
1647 } else if ((reader.name() == "application"_L1 ||
1648 reader.name() == "activity"_L1) &&
1649 reader.attributes().hasAttribute(qualifiedName: "android:label"_L1) &&
1650 reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "android:label"_L1) == "@string/app_name"_L1) {
1651 checkOldAndroidLabelString = true;
1652 } else if (reader.name() == "meta-data"_L1) {
1653 const auto name = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "android:name"_L1);
1654 const auto value = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "android:value"_L1);
1655 if (name == "android.app.lib_name"_L1 && value.contains(c: u' ')) {
1656 fprintf(stderr, format: "The Activity's android.app.lib_name should not contain"
1657 " spaces.\n");
1658 return false;
1659 }
1660 }
1661 }
1662 }
1663
1664 if (reader.hasError()) {
1665 fprintf(stderr, format: "Error in %s: %s\n", qPrintable(androidManifestPath), qPrintable(reader.errorString()));
1666 return false;
1667 }
1668 } else {
1669 fprintf(stderr, format: "No android manifest file");
1670 return false;
1671 }
1672
1673 if (checkOldAndroidLabelString)
1674 updateStringsXml(options);
1675
1676 return true;
1677}

1692
1693static QString absoluteFilePath(const Options *options, const QString &relativeFileName)
1694{
1695 // Use extraLibraryDirs as the extra library lookup folder if it is expected to find a file in
1696 // any $prefix/lib folder.
1697 // Library directories from a build tree(extraLibraryDirs) have the higher priority.
1698 if (relativeFileName.startsWith(s: "lib/"_L1)) {
1699 for (const auto &dir : options->extraLibraryDirs) {
1700 const QString path = dir + u'/' + relativeFileName.mid(position: sizeof("lib/") - 1);
1701 if (QFile::exists(fileName: path))
1702 return path;
1703 }
1704 }
1705
1706 for (const auto &prefix : options->extraPrefixDirs) {
1707 const QString path = prefix + u'/' + relativeFileName;
1708 if (QFile::exists(fileName: path))
1709 return path;
1710 }
1711 return options->qtInstallDirectory + u'/' + relativeFileName;
1712}
1713
1714QList<QtDependency> findFilesRecursively(const Options &options, const QFileInfo &info, const QString &rootPath)
1715{
1716 if (!info.exists())
1717 return QList<QtDependency>();
1718
1719 if (info.isDir()) {
1720 QList<QtDependency> ret;
1721
1722 QDir dir(info.filePath());
1723 const QStringList entries = dir.entryList(filters: QDir::Files | QDir::Dirs | QDir::NoDotAndDotDot);
1724
1725 for (const QString &entry : entries) {
1726 ret += findFilesRecursively(options,
1727 info: QFileInfo(info.absoluteFilePath() + QChar(u'/') + entry),
1728 rootPath);
1729 }
1730
1731 return ret;
1732 } else {
1733 return QList<QtDependency>() << QtDependency(info.absoluteFilePath().mid(position: rootPath.size()), info.absoluteFilePath());
1734 }
1735}
1736
1737QList<QtDependency> findFilesRecursively(const Options &options, const QString &fileName)
1738{
1739 for (const auto &prefix : options.extraPrefixDirs) {
1740 QFileInfo info(prefix + u'/' + fileName);
1741 if (info.exists())
1742 return findFilesRecursively(options, info, rootPath: prefix + u'/');
1743 }
1744 QFileInfo info(options.qtInstallDirectory + u'/' + fileName);
1745 return findFilesRecursively(options, info, rootPath: options.qtInstallDirectory + u'/');
1746}
1747
1748bool readAndroidDependencyXml(Options *options,
1749 const QString &moduleName,
1750 QSet<QString> *usedDependencies,
1751 QSet<QString> *remainingDependencies)
1752{
1753 QString androidDependencyName = absoluteFilePath(options, relativeFileName: "/lib/%1-android-dependencies.xml"_L1.arg(args: moduleName));
1754
1755 QFile androidDependencyFile(androidDependencyName);
1756 if (androidDependencyFile.exists()) {
1757 if (options->verbose)
1758 fprintf(stdout, format: "Reading Android dependencies for %s\n", qPrintable(moduleName));
1759
1760 if (!androidDependencyFile.open(flags: QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
1761 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot open %s for reading.\n", qPrintable(androidDependencyName));
1762 return false;
1763 }
1764
1765 QXmlStreamReader reader(&androidDependencyFile);
1766 while (!reader.atEnd()) {
1767 reader.readNext();
1768
1769 if (reader.isStartElement()) {
1770 if (reader.name() == "bundled"_L1) {
1771 if (!reader.attributes().hasAttribute(qualifiedName: "file"_L1)) {
1772 fprintf(stderr, format: "Invalid android dependency file: %s\n", qPrintable(androidDependencyName));
1773 return false;
1774 }
1775
1776 QString file = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "file"_L1).toString();
1777
1778 const QList<QtDependency> fileNames = findFilesRecursively(options: *options, fileName: file);
1779 for (const QtDependency &fileName : fileNames) {
1780 if (usedDependencies->contains(value: fileName.absolutePath))
1781 continue;
1782
1783 if (fileName.absolutePath.endsWith(s: ".so"_L1)) {
1784 QSet<QString> remainingDependencies;
1785 if (!readDependenciesFromElf(options, fileName: fileName.absolutePath,
1786 usedDependencies,
1787 remainingDependencies: &remainingDependencies)) {
1788 fprintf(stdout, format: "Skipping dependencies from xml: %s\n",
1789 qPrintable(fileName.relativePath));
1790 continue;
1791 }
1792 }
1793 usedDependencies->insert(value: fileName.absolutePath);
1794
1795 if (options->verbose)
1796 fprintf(stdout, format: "Appending dependency from xml: %s\n", qPrintable(fileName.relativePath));
1797
1798 options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture].append(t: fileName);
1799 }
1800 } else if (reader.name() == "jar"_L1) {
1801 int bundling = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "bundling"_L1).toInt();
1802 QString fileName = QDir::cleanPath(path: reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "file"_L1).toString());
1803 if (bundling) {
1804 QtDependency dependency(fileName, absoluteFilePath(options, relativeFileName: fileName));
1805 if (!usedDependencies->contains(value: dependency.absolutePath)) {
1806 options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture].append(t: dependency);
1807 usedDependencies->insert(value: dependency.absolutePath);
1808 }
1809 }
1810
1811 if (reader.attributes().hasAttribute(qualifiedName: "initClass"_L1)) {
1812 options->initClasses.append(t: reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "initClass"_L1).toString());
1813 }
1814 } else if (reader.name() == "lib"_L1) {
1815 QString fileName = QDir::cleanPath(path: reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "file"_L1).toString());
1816 if (reader.attributes().hasAttribute(qualifiedName: "replaces"_L1)) {
1817 QString replaces = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "replaces"_L1).toString();
1818 for (int i=0; i<options->localLibs.size(); ++i) {
1819 if (options->localLibs[options->currentArchitecture].at(i) == replaces) {
1820 options->localLibs[options->currentArchitecture][i] = fileName;
1821 break;
1822 }
1823 }
1824 } else if (!fileName.isEmpty()) {
1825 options->localLibs[options->currentArchitecture].append(t: fileName);
1826 }
1827 if (fileName.endsWith(s: ".so"_L1) && checkArchitecture(options: *options, fileName)) {
1828 remainingDependencies->insert(value: fileName);
1829 }
1830 } else if (reader.name() == "permission"_L1) {
1831 QString name = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "name"_L1).toString();
1832 options->permissions.append(t: name);
1833 } else if (reader.name() == "feature"_L1) {
1834 QString name = reader.attributes().value(qualifiedName: "name"_L1).toString();
1835 options->features.append(t: name);
1836 }
1837 }
1838 }
1839
1840 if (reader.hasError()) {
1841 fprintf(stderr, format: "Error in %s: %s\n", qPrintable(androidDependencyName), qPrintable(reader.errorString()));
1842 return false;
1843 }
1844 } else if (options->verbose) {
1845 fprintf(stdout, format: "No android dependencies for %s\n", qPrintable(moduleName));
1846 }
1847 options->permissions.removeDuplicates();
1848 options->features.removeDuplicates();
1849
1850 return true;

1852
1853QStringList getQtLibsFromElf(const Options &options, const QString &fileName)
1854{
1855 QString readElf = llvmReadobjPath(options);
1856 if (!QFile::exists(fileName: readElf)) {
1857 fprintf(stderr, format: "Command does not exist: %s\n", qPrintable(readElf));
1858 return QStringList();
1859 }
1860
1861 readElf = "%1 --needed-libs %2"_L1.arg(args: shellQuote(arg: readElf), args: shellQuote(arg: fileName));
1862
1863 FILE *readElfCommand = openProcess(command: readElf);
1864 if (!readElfCommand) {
1865 fprintf(stderr, format: "Cannot execute command %s\n", qPrintable(readElf));
1866 return QStringList();
1867 }
1868
1869 QStringList ret;
1870
1871 bool readLibs = false;
1872 char buffer[512];
1873 while (fgets(s: buffer, n: sizeof(buffer), stream: readElfCommand) != nullptr) {
1874 QByteArray line = QByteArray::fromRawData(data: buffer, size: qstrlen(str: buffer));
1875 QString library;
1876 line = line.trimmed();
1877 if (!readLibs) {
1878 if (line.startsWith(bv: "Arch: ")) {
1879 auto it = elfArchitectures.find(key: line.mid(index: 6));
1880 if (it == elfArchitectures.constEnd() || *it != options.currentArchitecture.toLatin1()) {
1881 if (options.verbose)
1882 fprintf(stdout, format: "Skipping \"%s\", architecture mismatch\n", qPrintable(fileName));
1883 return {};
1884 }
1885 }
1886 readLibs = line.startsWith(bv: "NeededLibraries");
1887 continue;
1888 }
1889 if (!line.startsWith(bv: "lib"))
1890 continue;
1891 library = QString::fromLatin1(ba: line);
1892 QString libraryName = "lib/"_L1 + library;
1893 if (QFile::exists(fileName: absoluteFilePath(options: &options, relativeFileName: libraryName)))
1894 ret += libraryName;
1895 }
1896
1897 pclose(stream: readElfCommand);
1898
1899 return ret;
1900}

1902bool readDependenciesFromElf(Options *options,
1903 const QString &fileName,
1904 QSet<QString> *usedDependencies,
1905 QSet<QString> *remainingDependencies)
1906{
1907 // Get dependencies on libraries in $QTDIR/lib
1908 const QStringList dependencies = getQtLibsFromElf(options: *options, fileName);
1909
1910 if (options->verbose) {
1911 fprintf(stdout, format: "Reading dependencies from %s\n", qPrintable(fileName));
1912 for (const QString &dep : dependencies)
1913 fprintf(stdout, format: " %s\n", qPrintable(dep));
1914 }
1915 // Recursively add dependencies from ELF and supplementary XML information
1916 QList<QString> dependenciesToCheck;
1917 for (const QString &dependency : dependencies) {
1918 if (usedDependencies->contains(value: dependency))
1919 continue;
1920
1921 QString absoluteDependencyPath = absoluteFilePath(options, relativeFileName: dependency);
1922 usedDependencies->insert(value: dependency);
1923 if (!readDependenciesFromElf(options,
1924 fileName: absoluteDependencyPath,
1925 usedDependencies,
1926 remainingDependencies)) {
1927 return false;
1928 }
1929
1930 options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture].append(t: QtDependency(dependency, absoluteDependencyPath));
1931 if (options->verbose)
1932 fprintf(stdout, format: "Appending dependency: %s\n", qPrintable(dependency));
1933 dependenciesToCheck.append(t: dependency);
1934 }
1935
1936 for (const QString &dependency : std::as_const(t&: dependenciesToCheck)) {
1937 QString qtBaseName = dependency.mid(position: sizeof("lib/lib") - 1);
1938 qtBaseName = qtBaseName.left(n: qtBaseName.size() - (sizeof(".so") - 1));
1939 if (!readAndroidDependencyXml(options, moduleName: qtBaseName, usedDependencies, remainingDependencies)) {
1940 return false;
1941 }
1942 }
1943
1944 return true;
1945}

1947bool scanImports(Options *options, QSet<QString> *usedDependencies)
1948{
1949 if (options->verbose)
1950 fprintf(stdout, format: "Scanning for QML imports.\n");
1951
1952 QString qmlImportScanner;
1953 if (!options->qmlImportScannerBinaryPath.isEmpty()) {
1954 qmlImportScanner = options->qmlImportScannerBinaryPath;
1955 } else {
1956 qmlImportScanner = execSuffixAppended(path: options->qtInstallDirectory + u'/'
1957 + defaultLibexecDir() + "/qmlimportscanner"_L1);
1958 }
1959
1960 QStringList importPaths;
1961
1962 // In Conan's case, qtInstallDirectory will point only to qtbase installed files, which
1963 // lacks a qml directory. We don't want to pass it as an import path if it doesn't exist
1964 // because it will cause qmlimportscanner to fail.
1965 // This also covers the case when only qtbase is installed in a regular Qt build.
1966 const QString mainImportPath = options->qtInstallDirectory + "/qml"_L1;
1967 if (QFile::exists(fileName: mainImportPath))
1968 importPaths += shellQuote(arg: mainImportPath);
1969
1970 // These are usually provided by CMake in the deployment json file from paths specified
1971 // in CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH. They might not have qml modules.
1972 for (const QString &prefix : options->extraPrefixDirs)
1973 if (QFile::exists(fileName: prefix + "/qml"_L1))
1974 importPaths += shellQuote(arg: prefix + "/qml"_L1);
1975
1976 // These are provided by both CMake and qmake.
1977 for (const QString &qmlImportPath : std::as_const(t&: options->qmlImportPaths)) {
1978 if (QFile::exists(fileName: qmlImportPath)) {
1979 importPaths += shellQuote(arg: qmlImportPath);
1980 } else {
1981 fprintf(stderr, format: "Warning: QML import path %s does not exist.\n",
1982 qPrintable(qmlImportPath));
1983 }
1984 }
1985
1986 bool qmlImportExists = false;
1987
1988 for (const QString &import : importPaths) {
1989 if (QDir().exists(name: import)) {
1990 qmlImportExists = true;
1991 break;
1992 }
1993 }
1994
1995 // Check importPaths without rootPath, since we need at least one qml plugins
1996 // folder to run a QML file
1997 if (!qmlImportExists) {
1998 fprintf(stderr, format: "Warning: no 'qml' directory found under Qt install directory "
1999 "or import paths. Skipping QML dependency scanning.\n");
2000 return true;
2001 }
2002
2003 if (!QFile::exists(fileName: qmlImportScanner)) {
2004 fprintf(stderr, format: "%s: qmlimportscanner not found at %s\n",
2005 qmlImportExists ? "Error"_L1.data() : "Warning"_L1.data(),
2006 qPrintable(qmlImportScanner));
2007 return true;
2008 }
2009
2010 for (auto rootPath : options->rootPaths) {
2011 rootPath = QFileInfo(rootPath).absoluteFilePath();
2012
2013 if (!rootPath.endsWith(c: u'/'))
2014 rootPath += u'/';
2015
2016 // After checking for qml folder imports we can add rootPath
2017 if (!rootPath.isEmpty())
2018 importPaths += shellQuote(arg: rootPath);
2019
2020 qmlImportScanner += " -rootPath %1"_L1.arg(args: shellQuote(arg: rootPath));
2021 }
2022
2023 if (!options->qrcFiles.isEmpty()) {
2024 qmlImportScanner += " -qrcFiles"_L1;
2025 for (const QString &qrcFile : options->qrcFiles)
2026 qmlImportScanner += u' ' + shellQuote(arg: qrcFile);
2027 }
2028
2029 qmlImportScanner += " -importPath %1"_L1.arg(args: importPaths.join(sep: u' '));
2030
2031 if (options->verbose) {
2032 fprintf(stdout, format: "Running qmlimportscanner with the following command: %s\n",
2033 qmlImportScanner.toLocal8Bit().constData());
2034 }
2035
2036 FILE *qmlImportScannerCommand = popen(command: qmlImportScanner.toLocal8Bit().constData(), QT_POPEN_READ);
2037 if (qmlImportScannerCommand == 0) {
2038 fprintf(stderr, format: "Couldn't run qmlimportscanner.\n");
2039 return false;
2040 }
2041
2042 QByteArray output;
2043 char buffer[512];
2044 while (fgets(s: buffer, n: sizeof(buffer), stream: qmlImportScannerCommand) != 0)
2045 output += QByteArray(buffer, qstrlen(str: buffer));
2046
2047 QJsonDocument jsonDocument = QJsonDocument::fromJson(json: output);
2048 if (jsonDocument.isNull()) {
2049 fprintf(stderr, format: "Invalid json output from qmlimportscanner.\n");
2050 return false;
2051 }
2052
2053 QJsonArray jsonArray = jsonDocument.array();
2054 for (int i=0; i<jsonArray.count(); ++i) {
2055 QJsonValue value = jsonArray.at(i);
2056 if (!value.isObject()) {
2057 fprintf(stderr, format: "Invalid format of qmlimportscanner output.\n");
2058 return false;
2059 }
2060
2061 QJsonObject object = value.toObject();
2062 QString path = object.value(key: "path"_L1).toString();
2063 if (path.isEmpty()) {
2064 fprintf(stderr, format: "Warning: QML import could not be resolved in any of the import paths: %s\n",
2065 qPrintable(object.value("name"_L1).toString()));
2066 } else {
2067 if (options->verbose)
2068 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Adding '%s' as QML dependency\n", qPrintable(path));
2069
2070 QFileInfo info(path);
2071
2072 // The qmlimportscanner sometimes outputs paths that do not exist.
2073 if (!info.exists()) {
2074 if (options->verbose)
2075 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Skipping because path does not exist.\n");
2076 continue;
2077 }
2078
2079 QString absolutePath = info.absolutePath();
2080 if (!absolutePath.endsWith(c: u'/'))
2081 absolutePath += u'/';
2082
2083 const QUrl url(object.value(key: "name"_L1).toString());
2084
2085 const QString moduleUrlPath = u"/"_s + url.toString().replace(before: u'.', after: u'/');
2086 if (checkCanImportFromRootPaths(options, absolutePath: info.absolutePath(), moduleUrl: moduleUrlPath)) {
2087 if (options->verbose)
2088 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Skipping because path is in QML root path.\n");
2089 continue;
2090 }
2091
2092 QString importPathOfThisImport;
2093 for (const QString &importPath : std::as_const(t&: importPaths)) {
2094 QString cleanImportPath = QDir::cleanPath(path: importPath);
2095 if (QFile::exists(fileName: cleanImportPath + moduleUrlPath)) {
2096 importPathOfThisImport = importPath;
2097 break;
2098 }
2099 }
2100
2101 if (importPathOfThisImport.isEmpty()) {
2102 fprintf(stderr, format: "Import found outside of import paths: %s.\n", qPrintable(info.absoluteFilePath()));
2103 return false;
2104 }
2105
2106 importPathOfThisImport = QDir(importPathOfThisImport).absolutePath() + u'/';
2107 QList<QtDependency> qmlImportsDependencies;
2108 auto collectQmlDependency = [&usedDependencies, &qmlImportsDependencies,
2109 &importPathOfThisImport](const QString &filePath) {
2110 if (!usedDependencies->contains(value: filePath)) {
2111 usedDependencies->insert(value: filePath);
2112 qmlImportsDependencies += QtDependency(
2113 "qml/"_L1 + filePath.mid(position: importPathOfThisImport.size()),
2114 filePath);
2115 }
2116 };
2117
2118 QString plugin = object.value(key: "plugin"_L1).toString();
2119 bool pluginIsOptional = object.value(key: "pluginIsOptional"_L1).toBool();
2120 QFileInfo pluginFileInfo = QFileInfo(
2121 path + u'/' + "lib"_L1 + plugin + u'_'
2122 + options->currentArchitecture + ".so"_L1);
2123 QString pluginFilePath = pluginFileInfo.absoluteFilePath();
2124 QSet<QString> remainingDependencies;
2125 if (pluginFileInfo.exists() && checkArchitecture(options: *options, fileName: pluginFilePath)
2126 && readDependenciesFromElf(options, fileName: pluginFilePath, usedDependencies,
2127 remainingDependencies: &remainingDependencies)) {
2128 collectQmlDependency(pluginFilePath);
2129 } else if (!pluginIsOptional) {
2130 if (options->verbose)
2131 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Skipping because the required plugin is missing.\n");
2132 continue;
2133 }
2134
2135 QFileInfo qmldirFileInfo = QFileInfo(path + u'/' + "qmldir"_L1);
2136 if (qmldirFileInfo.exists()) {
2137 collectQmlDependency(qmldirFileInfo.absoluteFilePath());
2138 }
2139
2140 QString prefer = object.value(key: "prefer"_L1).toString();
2141 // If the preferred location of Qml files points to the Qt resources, this means
2142 // that all Qml files has been embedded into plugin and we should not copy them to the
2143 // android rcc bundle
2144 if (!prefer.startsWith(s: ":/"_L1)) {
2145 QVariantList qmlFiles =
2146 object.value(key: "components"_L1).toArray().toVariantList();
2147 qmlFiles.append(l: object.value(key: "scripts"_L1).toArray().toVariantList());
2148 bool qmlFilesMissing = false;
2149 for (const auto &qmlFileEntry : qmlFiles) {
2150 QFileInfo fileInfo(qmlFileEntry.toString());
2151 if (!fileInfo.exists()) {
2152 qmlFilesMissing = true;
2153 break;
2154 }
2155 collectQmlDependency(fileInfo.absoluteFilePath());
2156 }
2157
2158 if (qmlFilesMissing) {
2159 if (options->verbose)
2160 fprintf(stdout,
2161 format: " -- Skipping because the required qml files are missing.\n");
2162 continue;
2163 }
2164 }
2165
2166 options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture].append(l: qmlImportsDependencies);
2167 }
2168 }
2169
2170 return true;
2171}

2176 for (auto rootPath : options->rootPaths) {
2177 if ((rootPath + moduleUrlPath) == absolutePath)
2178 return true;

2258bool readDependencies(Options *options)
2259{
2260 if (options->verbose)
2261 fprintf(stdout, format: "Detecting dependencies of application.\n");
2262
2263 // Override set in .pro file
2264 if (!options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture].isEmpty()) {
2265 if (options->verbose)
2266 fprintf(stdout, format: "\tDependencies explicitly overridden in .pro file. No detection needed.\n");
2267 return true;
2268 }
2269
2270 QSet<QString> usedDependencies;
2271 QSet<QString> remainingDependencies;
2272
2273 // Add dependencies of application binary first
2274 if (!readDependenciesFromElf(options, fileName: "%1/libs/%2/lib%3_%2.so"_L1.arg(args&: options->outputDirectory, args&: options->currentArchitecture, args&: options->applicationBinary), usedDependencies: &usedDependencies, remainingDependencies: &remainingDependencies))
2275 return false;
2276
2277 while (!remainingDependencies.isEmpty()) {
2278 QSet<QString>::iterator start = remainingDependencies.begin();
2279 QString fileName = absoluteFilePath(options, relativeFileName: *start);
2280 remainingDependencies.erase(i: start);
2281
2282 QStringList unmetDependencies;
2283 if (goodToCopy(options, file: fileName, unmetDependencies: &unmetDependencies)) {
2284 bool ok = readDependenciesFromElf(options, fileName, usedDependencies: &usedDependencies, remainingDependencies: &remainingDependencies);
2285 if (!ok)
2286 return false;

2288 fprintf(stdout, format: "Skipping %s due to unmet dependencies: %s\n",
2289 qPrintable(fileName),
2290 qPrintable(unmetDependencies.join(u',')));
2291 }
2292 }
2293
2294 QStringList::iterator it = options->localLibs[options->currentArchitecture].begin();
2295 while (it != options->localLibs[options->currentArchitecture].end()) {
2296 QStringList unmetDependencies;
2297 if (!goodToCopy(options, file: absoluteFilePath(options, relativeFileName: *it), unmetDependencies: &unmetDependencies)) {
2298 fprintf(stdout, format: "Skipping %s due to unmet dependencies: %s\n",
2299 qPrintable(*it),
2300 qPrintable(unmetDependencies.join(u',')));
2301 it = options->localLibs[options->currentArchitecture].erase(pos: it);
2302 } else {
2303 ++it;
2304 }
2305 }
2306
2307 if (options->qmlSkipImportScanning
2308 || (options->rootPaths.empty() && options->qrcFiles.isEmpty()))

2310 return scanImports(options, usedDependencies: &usedDependencies);

2388bool copyQtFiles(Options *options)
2389{
2390 if (options->verbose) {
2391 switch (options->deploymentMechanism) {
2392 case Options::Bundled:
2393 fprintf(stdout, format: "Copying %zd dependencies from Qt into package.\n", size_t(options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture].size()));
2394 break;
2395 case Options::Unbundled:
2396 fprintf(stdout, format: "Copying dependencies from Qt into the package build folder,"
2397 "skipping native libraries.\n");
2398 break;
2399 };
2400 }
2401
2402 if (!options->build)
2403 return true;
2404
2405
2406 QString libsDirectory = "libs/"_L1;
2407
2408 // Copy other Qt dependencies
2409 auto assetsDestinationDirectory = "assets/android_rcc_bundle/"_L1;
2410 for (const QtDependency &qtDependency : std::as_const(t&: options->qtDependencies[options->currentArchitecture])) {
2411 QString sourceFileName = qtDependency.absolutePath;
2412 QString destinationFileName;
2413 bool isSharedLibrary = qtDependency.relativePath.endsWith(s: ".so"_L1);
2414 if (isSharedLibrary) {
2415 QString garbledFileName;
2416 if (QDir::fromNativeSeparators(pathName: qtDependency.relativePath).startsWith(s: "lib/"_L1)) {
2417 garbledFileName = qtDependency.relativePath.mid(position: sizeof("lib/") - 1);
2418 } else {
2419 garbledFileName = qtDependency.relativePath.mid(position: qtDependency.relativePath.lastIndexOf(c: u'/') + 1);
2420 }
2421 destinationFileName = libsDirectory + options->currentArchitecture + u'/' + garbledFileName;
2422 } else if (QDir::fromNativeSeparators(pathName: qtDependency.relativePath).startsWith(s: "jar/"_L1)) {
2423 destinationFileName = libsDirectory + qtDependency.relativePath.mid(position: sizeof("jar/") - 1);
2424 } else {
2425 destinationFileName = assetsDestinationDirectory + qtDependency.relativePath;
2426 }
2427
2428 if (!QFile::exists(fileName: sourceFileName)) {
2429 fprintf(stderr, format: "Source Qt file does not exist: %s.\n", qPrintable(sourceFileName));
2430 return false;
2431 }
2432
2433 QStringList unmetDependencies;
2434 if (!goodToCopy(options, file: sourceFileName, unmetDependencies: &unmetDependencies)) {
2435 if (unmetDependencies.isEmpty()) {
2436 if (options->verbose) {
2437 fprintf(stdout, format: " -- Skipping %s, architecture mismatch.\n",
2438 qPrintable(sourceFileName));
2439 }

2446 }

2507typedef QMap<QByteArray, QByteArray> GradleProperties;
2508
2509static GradleProperties readGradleProperties(const QString &path)
2510{
2511 GradleProperties properties;
2512 QFile file(path);
2513 if (!file.open(flags: QIODevice::ReadOnly))
2514 return properties;
2515
2516 const auto lines = file.readAll().split(sep: '\n');
2517 for (const QByteArray &line : lines) {
2518 if (line.trimmed().startsWith(c: '#'))
2519 continue;
2520
2521 const int idx = line.indexOf(c: '=');
2522 if (idx > -1)
2523 properties[line.left(len: idx).trimmed()] = line.mid(index: idx + 1).trimmed();
2524 }
2525 file.close();
2526 return properties;
2527}

2529static bool mergeGradleProperties(const QString &path, GradleProperties properties)
2530{
2531 const QString oldPathStr = path + u'~';
2532 QFile::remove(fileName: oldPathStr);
2533 QFile::rename(oldName: path, newName: oldPathStr);
2534 QFile file(path);
2535 if (!file.open(flags: QIODevice::Truncate | QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text)) {
2536 fprintf(stderr, format: "Can't open file: %s for writing\n", qPrintable(file.fileName()));
2537 return false;
2538 }
2539
2540 QFile oldFile(oldPathStr);
2541 if (oldFile.open(flags: QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
2542 while (!oldFile.atEnd()) {
2543 QByteArray line(oldFile.readLine());
2544 QList<QByteArray> prop(line.split(sep: '='));
2545 if (prop.size() > 1) {
2546 GradleProperties::iterator it = properties.find(key: prop.at(i: 0).trimmed());
2547 if (it != properties.end()) {
2548 file.write(data: it.key() + '=' + it.value() + '\n');
2549 properties.erase(it);
2550 continue;
2551 }
2552 }
2553 file.write(data: line.trimmed() + '\n');
2554 }
2555 oldFile.close();
2556 QFile::remove(fileName: oldPathStr);
2557 }
2558
2559 for (GradleProperties::const_iterator it = properties.begin(); it != properties.end(); ++it)
2560 file.write(data: it.key() + '=' + it.value() + '\n');
2561
2562 file.close();
2563 return true;
2564}

3037 .arg(args: shellQuote(arg: apksignerTool), args: shellQuote(arg: packagePath(options, pt: SignedAPK)));
3038
3039 if (options.buildAAB && !signAAB(options))
3040 return false;
3041
3042 // Verify the package and remove the unsigned apk
3043 return apkSignerRunner(apkVerifyCommand, true) && QFile::remove(fileName: packagePath(options, pt: UnsignedAPK));

3068bool writeDependencyFile(const Options &options)
3069{
3070 if (options.verbose)
3071 fprintf(stdout, format: "Writing dependency file.\n");
3072
3073 QString relativeTargetPath;
3074 if (options.copyDependenciesOnly) {
3075 // When androiddeploy Qt is running in copyDependenciesOnly mode we need to use
3076 // the timestamp file as the target to collect dependencies.
3077 QString timestampAbsPath = QFileInfo(options.depFilePath).absolutePath() + "/timestamp"_L1;
3078 relativeTargetPath = QDir(options.buildDirectory).relativeFilePath(fileName: timestampAbsPath);
3079 } else {
3080 relativeTargetPath = QDir(options.buildDirectory).relativeFilePath(fileName: options.apkPath);
3081 }
3082
3083 QFile depFile(options.depFilePath);
3084 if (depFile.open(flags: QIODevice::WriteOnly)) {
3085 depFile.write(data: escapeAndEncodeDependencyPath(path: relativeTargetPath));
3086 depFile.write(data: ": ");
3087
3088 for (const auto &file : dependenciesForDepfile) {
3089 depFile.write(data: " \\\n ");
3090 depFile.write(data: escapeAndEncodeDependencyPath(path: file));
3091 }
3092
3093 depFile.write(data: "\n");
3094 }
3095 return true;
3096}
